attrs.doc: Parses, resolves, and typechecks the given crate
A newtype struct (tuple struct with one element)
Name is optional for tuple structs

A representation of a Type suitable for hyperlinking purposes. Ideally one can get the original type out of the AST/ty::ctxt given one of these, if more information is needed. Most importantly it does not preserve mutability or boxes.
Most types start out as "Unresolved". It serves as an intermediate stage between cleaning and type resolution.
For parameterized types, so the consumer of the JSON don't go looking for types which don't exist anywhere.
Primitives are just the fixed-size numeric types (plus int/uint/float), and char.
Given a Type, resolve it using the def_map
This is a more limited form of the standard Struct, different in that it it lacks the things most items have (name, id, parameterization). Found only as a variant in an enum.
